			<abstract>Toponymy is the study of place-names, based on etymological, historical and geographical information. This research tries to have a derivational morphology survey on toponyms of Hamedan province. The main discussion proposes a true method to analyze toponyms based on derivational morphology and historical linguistics point of view. This paper gives many applied affixes supported by clear examples. Since toponyms have been subjected to many linguistic changes throughout the history, this paper focuses on the syntactic structure analysis. There is also a new function proposed for the affixes which are found in the toponyms studied in this research.</abstract>
